Holiness. Mistakes have been made in regard to what constitutes sanctification and holiness. This is claimed by many who have no right to it; 


                                    -318- 

for while they claim and teach purity, their own course of action belies their profession. They mislead minds, and their course of conduct testifies that they are doing the works of the enemy. We are called into the freedom of the gospel but not into the service of sin. We are called to wear Christ's yoke, which is true liberty, not liberty to sin and disregard the plainest injunction of the Word of God, "If ye love Me, keep My commandments."
